The SA Weather Service said that temperatures were expected to peak from Thursday into next week. JOHANNESBURG - Despite the cool weather on Wednesday, Gauteng residents are being warned to prepare for another heatwave. The SA Weather Service said that temperatures were expected to peak from Thursday into next week. Last weekend saw temperatures reach 36 degrees Celsius in Johannesburg and a scorching 41 degrees Celsius in other parts of the country. Forecaster Mbavhi Maliage: "Some places will start [to feel the heat] on Friday but the majority of the areas, especially in Gauteng and Mpumalanga will start on Saturday, pushing over into Monday."